snippet.textDisplay: As excited as I am for a new LEGO Star Wars game, I can not say I’m going to purchase the game. The last three LEGO games I’ve played, Star Wars TFA, hobbit, and movie, all had game breaking, downright unacceptable glitches that completely ruin the experience. And their customer support isn’t at all helpful. I’m probably the only one who’s had a problem with the LEGO games, but I do want to voice the opinion as someone who would’ve loved this announcement if I hadn’t played LEGO games since before 2010.
snippet.textOriginal: As excited as I am for a new LEGO Star Wars game, I can not say I’m going to purchase the game. The last three LEGO games I’ve played, Star Wars TFA, hobbit, and movie, all had game breaking, downright unacceptable glitches that completely ruin the experience. And their customer support isn’t at all helpful. I’m probably the only one who’s had a problem with the LEGO games, but I do want to voice the opinion as someone who would’ve loved this announcement if I hadn’t played LEGO games since before 2010.
